==Verb==

===Pronunciation===
*chor·li·an, ye·chor·li·an

Note: this verb may appear with or without the [[ge-]] prefix, without a change in meaning

===Definition===
# to marry, take a husband; ''used of a woman''

===Declension===
*Class 2 Weak Transitive Verb

====Present Tense====

=====Indicative=====
*Singular: ic ceorlie, þu ceorlast, hé ceorlaþ
*Plural: wé, gé, híe ceorliaþ

=====Subjunctive=====
*Singular: ceorlie
*Plural: ceorlien

=====Imperative=====
*Singular: ceorla!
*Plural: ceorliaþ!

=====Participle=====
*ceorliende

====Past Tense====

=====Indicative=====
*Singular: ic ceorlode, þu ceorlodest, hé ceorlode
*Plural: wé, gé, híe ceorlodon

=====Subjunctive=====
*Singular: ceorlode
*Plural: ceorloden

=====Participle=====
*geceorlod

====Inflected Infinitive====
*tó ceorlienne

===Etymology===
*Derived from [[ceorl]] ''m'', ''man, husband''.

